body:
Please understand that this is a popular project, useful to many learners, and empty PRs distract maintainers that are trying to help others.

If you would like practice with PRs, or teach your students how to raise PR, you can follow github documentation to create your own repo:
https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/creating-a-new-repository
And then in that repo practice creating and editing PRs:
https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/proposing-changes-to-your-work-with-pull-requests/creating-a-pull-request

We look forward to your future contributions to OSSU, when you are contributing to improve data science education for learners all over the world!
Thanks for the suggestion @TinhToQuang ! It's been incorporated into the curriculum.
